DTSTAMP:20260303T114022Z
DTSTART:20260323T145200Z
DTEND:20260323T145700Z
SUMMARY:Project Lightning Talk: Safe By Design: AI-Powered Auto-Healing For SREs - Arik Alon\, Maintainer
DESCRIPTION:As cloud-native and distributed systems grow in scale and complexity\, traditional incident response can’t keep up. AI-driven root cause analysis is transforming how SREs identify issues. But what about automatically remediating them?\n\nIn this session\, we’ll explore the next step: AI-powered remediation with safety and confidence built in. You’ll learn how to transition from insights to actions\, using guardrails\, validations\, and approval workflows that let your team trust an autonomous system without fear of unintended consequences.\n\nWe’ll cover:\n- Moving from detection and root cause analysis to automated healing in cloud-native systems\n- Designing safe\, controlled remediation pipelines for distributed environments\n- Building confidence in AI-driven fixes across production infrastructure\n\nAttendees will leave with practical strategies for starting with pre-approved\, human-in-the-loop remediation and gradually transitioning to fully autonomous\, self-healing systems.
CATEGORIES:PROJECT OPPORTUNITIES
LOCATION:Elicium 2\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:2cca3349a4574a0a8ae613fa6548a4ab
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/2cca3349a4574a0a8ae613fa6548a4ab
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260303T114022Z
DTSTART:20260323T145900Z
DTEND:20260323T150400Z
SUMMARY:Project Lightning Talk: OpenCost: Cost And Resource Management - Warwich Peatey\, Maintainer
DESCRIPTION:Join us as we cover the OpenCost project (incubating in the CNCF) and how you can get granular cost metrics from your Kubernetes cluster in the cloud and on-prem.\nWe’ll also cover the OpenCost MCP server\, how you can do health tracking and diagnostics\, OpenCost’s KubeModel\, and a how to get started.
CATEGORIES:PROJECT OPPORTUNITIES
LOCATION:Elicium 2\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:714fd19d7c75843e2de193056e7a7afc
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/714fd19d7c75843e2de193056e7a7afc
