SUMMARY:Sponsored Demo: Tailor-Made Nodes on GKE with Compute Classes
DESCRIPTION:In the era of specialized hardware\, "one size fits all" is a recipe for resource wastage and performance bottlenecks. Enter Compute Classes\, an API that allows platform engineers to define bespoke infrastructure templates for specific workloads. Beyond simple selection\, Compute Classes introduces a prioritization engine for machine types. Whether you are hunting for the perfect CPU-to-memory ratio for high-frequency trading or optimizing GPU attachments for LLM inference\, Custom Compute Classes provide the abstraction layer needed to scale without the friction of manual node pool management. In this demo-heavy session\, we will: - Explore the architecture of Custom Compute Classes. - Demonstrate "Just-in-Time" infrastructure provisioning. - Reveal how to automate the lifecycle of specialized hardware - Configuring machine type priority to balance performance vs. availability. **In order to facilitate networking and business relationships at the event\, you may choose to visit a third party’s booth or access sponsored content. You are never required to visit third party booths or to access sponsored content. When visiting a booth or participating in sponsored activities\, the third party will receive some of your registration data. This data includes your first name\, last name\, title\, company\, address\, email\, standard demographics questions (i.e. job function\, industry)\, and details about the sponsored content or resources you interacted with. If you choose to interact with a booth or access sponsored content\, you are explicitly consenting to receipt and use of such data by the third-party recipients\, which will be subject to their own privacy policies.**
CATEGORIES:SOLUTIONS SHOWCASE
LOCATION:Halls 1-5\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
