DTSTAMP:20260303T114022Z
DTSTART:20260324T110000Z
DTEND:20260324T113000Z
SUMMARY:Your Models Are Vulnerable: How KitOps Turns KServe Into a Zero-Trust Inference Platform - Brad Micklea\, Jozu & Gavrish Prabhu\, Nutanix
DESCRIPTION:Model serving on KServe is easy. Proving your model hasn't been poisoned\, tampered with\, or swapped? That's where things fall apart. This talk reveals how KitOps transforms KServe into a zero-trust inference platform using ModelKits: OCI-native bundles that package models\, datasets\, code\, and configs with cryptographic signatures - stored in the registry you already run. No new infrastructure\, no vendor lock-in. We'll expose real ML-pipeline attack vectors and demonstrate production patterns that shut them down: init containers that verify model signatures\, OPA policies blocking unattested models\, and GitOps with a cryptographic chain‑of‑custody from training to production. You'll leave with battle-tested manifests\, demos\, and a deployment checklist that DSV (160K employees) and federal labs already use. Whether you're facing auditors tomorrow or just want to sleep better knowing your AI hasn't been compromised\, you'll learn how to harden KServe today using tools you already have.
CATEGORIES:AI + ML
LOCATION:Auditorium\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:a9670815dd9716f90a5f939beea5b5b9
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/a9670815dd9716f90a5f939beea5b5b9
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260303T114022Z
DTSTART:20260324T110000Z
DTEND:20260324T113000Z
SUMMARY:Virtual Power Plants (VPP): How They Work and What They Are - LeRenzo Malcom & Mario Flores\, Enpal
DESCRIPTION:Virtual Power Plants (VPPs) are reshaping the energy grid by turning thousands of distributed IoT devices—solar systems\, batteries\, EV chargers—into one coordinated\, cloud-native asset. At Enpal\, we operate one of Europe’s largest residential solar fleets and are building a next-generation VPP platform to orchestrate it.\n\nThis talk explores what it really means to build a power plant in software—and why developing for IoT looks nothing like typical cloud app development.\n\nYou’ll learn:\n\n1. How a Virtual Power Plant works—from household solar to market bidding\n\n2. Why IoT development differs from regular cloud systems (latency\, autonomy\, bandwidth\, lifecycle control)\n\n3. How Enpal’s IoT and cloud systems coordinate to optimize energy use and revenue in real time\n\n4. What design patterns (Kubernetes\, KubeEdge\, Dapr\, event streaming) make it possible to treat 100\,000+ homes like a distributed cluster\n\n5. How VPPs make money—through flexibility markets\, load shifting\, and price arbitrage
CATEGORIES:APPLICATION DEVELOPMENT
LOCATION:Hall 8 | Room E\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:481d9a8fadd5e5e3385cfbf1fe3d101e
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/481d9a8fadd5e5e3385cfbf1fe3d101e
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260303T114022Z
DTSTART:20260324T110000Z
DTEND:20260324T113000Z
SUMMARY:Cloud Native Non-Functional Requirements: Building Scalable\, Resilient and Secure Applications - Jakub Krzywda\, Elastisys
DESCRIPTION:In software development\, we often focus on functional requirements – what the application does. But let’s be real: it’s the non-functional requirements (NFRs) that make or break an application’s success in the long run. For cloud-native applications\, things like scalability\, resilience\, observability\, and security aren’t just “nice-to-haves” – they’re the foundation of performance\, maintainability\, and availability.\n\nThat’s why we’re hosting an in-depth session to dive into the NFRs every cloud-native developer needs to master. We’ll cover:\n• Microservice architecture for scalability and fault tolerance\n• Build and deployment automation to keep releases smooth and stress-free\n• State and configuration management to ensure resilience and uptime across environments\n• Observability and high availability for reliability and rapid troubleshooting\n\nThis session will provide developers with practical insights on how to build applications\, which are not only functional – but built to last.
CATEGORIES:CLOUD NATIVE NOVICE
LOCATION:Hall 7 | Room A\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:420e335e851a485e100c7cbe96ae0ff9
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/420e335e851a485e100c7cbe96ae0ff9
END:VEVENT
