SUMMARY:Cloud Native Theater | Cloud Native University: Platform Engineering - About Tools\, Techniques\, People and Culture - Max Körbächer\, Liquid Reply
DESCRIPTION:Platform Engineering is all over the place\, at the same time many people approaches us saying they have heard it at KubeCon the first time. So\, let us explore how platforms aren't just infrastructure. They're products that combine tools\, automation\, and self-service capabilities to make developers' and other personas lives easier. \n I'll demystify core concepts: what platforms actually do\, why they matter in cloud-native environments\, and how they reduce complexity rather than add another layer.\n But great platforms aren't built on technology alone. We'll explore the often-overlooked human side: understanding user needs\, fostering collaboration\, and cultivating a platform-centric culture through training\, community building\, and advocacy. \n You'll learn why platforms succeed or fail based on how well they respect the socio-technical system\, where technology meets people\, workflows\, and organizational culture.
CATEGORIES:SOLUTIONS SHOWCASE
LOCATION:Hall 1-5 | Tram Zone | Cloud Native Theater\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
