SUMMARY:Cloud Native Theater | EnvoyCon: Powering User-Facing GenAI at Bloomberg with Envoy AI Gateway: A Hybrid Cloud Approach - Xiaolin Lin\, Bloomberg
DESCRIPTION:The rapid rise of Generative AI (GenAI) and large language models (LLMs) is transforming how end users interact with financial data—but deploying these capabilities in production presents unique challenges. Financial services firms must deliver low-latency\, highly reliable GenAI experiences while meeting strict requirements around data governance\, security\, and regulatory compliance\, often across a mix of on-prem and cloud-based models. \n\nIn this talk\, we’ll share how Bloomberg uses Envoy AI Gateway\, a CNCF-hosted open source project\, as a core building block of our GenAI platform to safely and efficiently serve user-facing AI workloads for 100+ teams. \n\nWe’ll walk through our journey from concept to production\, focusing on how Envoy AI Gateway enables consistent\, scalable access to LLMs powering real-time financial applications. \n\nWe’ll highlight how features such as secure authentication\, intelligent model routing\, and token-based rate limiting help us deliver responsive GenAI experiences to end users while improving performance\, resilience\, and operational simplicity.
CATEGORIES:SOLUTIONS SHOWCASE
LOCATION:Hall 1-5 | Tram Zone | Cloud Native Theater\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
