SUMMARY:Sponsored Demo: The theory and practice of sampling in OpenTelemetry
DESCRIPTION:Distributed tracing is the most expressive observability signal\, as well as the most expensive. A modest microservices deployment can produce millions of spans per minute. While storage costs have decreased over time\, our ability to query and derive value from spans at scale has not kept pace. Sampling is the answer\, but choosing the right strategy involves real trade-offs that are poorly documented and hard to implement outside vendor ecosystems. In this session\, we explore sampling through the lens of OpenTelemetry's community resources: head and tail sampling\, probabilistic vs. rate-limiting approaches\, the statefulness challenges of tail sampling at scale\, and the often-overlooked impact of sampling on connected concepts like RED metrics. Attendees will leave with a practical framework for choosing and configuring a sampling strategy that balances cost\, completeness\, and metric accuracy. **In order to facilitate networking and business relationships at the event\, you may choose to visit a third party’s booth or access sponsored content. You are never required to visit third party booths or to access sponsored content. When visiting a booth or participating in sponsored activities\, the third party will receive some of your registration data. This data includes your first name\, last name\, title\, company\, address\, email\, standard demographics questions (i.e. job function\, industry)\, and details about the sponsored content or resources you interacted with. If you choose to interact with a booth or access sponsored content\, you are explicitly consenting to receipt and use of such data by the third-party recipients\, which will be subject to their own privacy policies.**
CATEGORIES:SOLUTIONS SHOWCASE
LOCATION:Halls 1-5\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
