SUMMARY:Harbor Project - The Maintainers Session - Yan Wang\, Broadcom & Vadim Bauer\, 8gears
DESCRIPTION:Harbor continues to evolve as a core cloud-native registry\, supporting secure and scalable software delivery across Kubernetes environments. In this maintainer update\, we’ll highlight key improvements from Harbor 2.14 and 2.15\, shaped by operator and community feedback. \n \n The session will cover notable enhancements in security\, registry operations\, and day-2 manageability\, along with important architectural and API changes relevant to platform teams\, integrators\, and contributors. We’ll also touch on how recent releases improve upgradeability\, performance\, and ecosystem integration. \n \n To close\, we’ll look ahead at what’s coming next for Harbor\, including upcoming roadmap items\, active design discussions\, and ways for the community to get involved. Attendees will leave with a clear view of where Harbor stands today and how they can help shape its future.
CATEGORIES:MAINTAINER TRACK
LOCATION:E103-105\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
